title: Mary Marston
creator: George MacDonald
description: LibriVox recording of Mary Marston, by George MacDonald. Written at the height of George MacDonald's literary career, the story centers around the life of a simple merchant's daughter. Mary Marston's unswerving commitment to love, God, and others is contrasted with a backdrop of an array of characters and a complex and sometimes mysterious plot. It is a story of a woman who loves a man, and teaches him to change. Not out of his love for her, but simply because it was the right thing to do. MacDonald allows the characters a range from delightful to devious. As such, they were intended to serve as models. His message is that all eventually must stand before God. (Summary text from Wikipedia) Download M4B Part 1 (140MB) Download M4B Part 2 (105MB) Download M4B Part 3 (119MB) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; fiction; romance
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: I love the works of George MacDonald and was delighted to find a recording of Mary Marston. However, I must offer a warning to other listeners who, like me, listen to books using headphones. Some chapters are a bit hard on the ears. I was forced to skip several. The novel is read by several readers and quality of audio varies. Being such a fan of MacDonald, and believing his work deserves wider readership, this was particularly disappointing.
